1086 class action_on_factor_space {
1087 public:
1088  void *operator new(size_t bytes);
1089  void *operator new[](size_t bytes);
1090  void operator delete(void *ptr, size_t bytes);
1091  void operator delete[](void *ptr, size_t bytes);
1092  static INT cntr_new;
1093  static INT cntr_objects;
1094  static INT f_debug_memory;
1095 
1096  INT len; // length of vectors in large space
1097  finite_field *F;
1098  INT *subspace_basis; // [subspace_basis_size * len]
1099  INT subspace_basis_size;
1100  INT *base_cols; // [subspace_basis_size]
1101  // the pivot column for the subspace basis
1102  // to be used if a vector v[len] is reduced modulo a subspace
1103 
1104  INT degree;
1105  // the number of projective points in the small space (i.e., the factor space)
1106  // (q^factor_space_len - 1) / (q - 1),
1107  // as computed by compute_degree();
1108  INT large_degree;
1109  // the number of projective points in the large space
1110  // (q^len - 1) / (q - 1),
1111  // as computed by compute_large_degree();
1112 
1113  INT factor_space_len;
1114  // = len - subspace_basis_size
1115 
1116  INT *embedding;
1117  // [factor_space_len]
1118  // the list of columns that are not pivot columns, i.e. not in base_cols[]
1119  // this is the set-theoretic complement of base_cols
1120  INT *projection_table;
1121  // [nb_points]
1122  // projection_table[i] = j
1123  // menas that the Gauss reduced vector in the coset of point_list[i]
1124  // is in coset_reps_Gauss[j]
1125  INT *preimage_table; // [degree]
1126  INT *tmp; // [factor_space_len]
1127  INT *Tmp1; // [len]
1128  INT *Tmp2; // [len]
1129  INT f_tables_have_been_computed;
1130 
1131  INT f_table_mode;
1132  INT f_has_rank_function;
1133  INT (*rank_point_func)(INT *v, void *data);
1134  void (*unrank_point_func)(INT *v, INT rk, void *data);
1135  void *rank_point_data;
1136  INT nb_cosets;
1137  INT *coset_reps_Gauss;
1138  // [nb_cosets]
1139  // ordered list of Gauss reduced coset representatives
1140  // the entries are ranks of vectors in the large space
1141 
1142  INT *tmp_w; // [len] temporary vector for use in rank
1143  INT *tmp_w1; // [subspace_basis_size] temporary vector for lexleast_element_in_coset
1144  INT *tmp_v1; // [len] temporary vector for use in lexleast_element_in_coset
1145  INT *tmp_v2; // [len] temporary vector for use in lexleast_element_in_coset
1146 
1147  action_on_factor_space();
1148  ~action_on_factor_space();
1149  void null();
1150  void free();
1151  void init_light(action &A_base, action &A, INT len, finite_field *F,
1152  INT *subspace_basis_ranks, INT subspace_basis_size,
1153  INT (*rank_point_func)(INT *v, void *data),
1154  void (*unrank_point_func)(INT *v, INT rk, void *data),
1155  void *rank_point_data,
1156  INT verbose_level);
1157  void init_by_rank_table_mode(action &A_base, action &A, INT len, finite_field *F,
1158  INT *subspace_basis_ranks, INT subspace_basis_size,
1159  INT *point_list, INT nb_points,
1160  INT (*rank_point_func)(INT *v, void *data),
1161  void (*unrank_point_func)(INT *v, INT rk, void *data),
1162  void *rank_point_data,
1163  INT verbose_level);
1164  void init_by_rank(action &A_base, action &A, INT len, finite_field *F,
1165  INT *subspace_basis_ranks, INT subspace_basis_size, INT f_compute_tables, INT verbose_level);
1166  void init_from_coordinate_vectors(action &A_base, action &A, INT len, finite_field *F,
1167  INT *subspace_basis, INT subspace_basis_size, INT f_compute_tables, INT verbose_level);
1168  void init2(action &A_base, action &A, INT f_compute_tables, INT verbose_level);
1169  void compute_projection_table(INT verbose_level);
1170  INT compute_degree();
1171  INT compute_large_degree();
1172  void list_all_elements();
1173  void reduce_mod_subspace(INT *v, INT verbose_level);
1174  INT lexleast_element_in_coset(INT rk, INT verbose_level);
1175  // This function computes the lexleast element in the coset modulo the subspace.
1176  // It does so by looping over all q^subspace_basis_size
1177  // elements in the subspace and ranking the corresponding
1178  // vector in the large space using rank_in_large_space(v2).
1179  INT project_onto_Gauss_reduced_vector(INT rk, INT verbose_level);
1180  INT project(INT rk, INT verbose_level);
1181  // unranks the vector rk, and reduces it modiulo the subspace basis.
1182  // The non-pivot components are considered as a vector in F_q^factor_space_len
1183  // and ranked using the rank function for projective space.
1184  // This rank is returned.
1185  // If the vector turns out to lie in the subspace, a -1 is returned.
1186  INT preimage(INT rk, INT verbose_level);
1187  void unrank(INT *v, INT rk, INT verbose_level);
1188  INT rank(INT *v, INT verbose_level);
1189  void unrank_in_large_space(INT *v, INT rk);
1190  INT rank_in_large_space(INT *v);
1191  INT compute_image(action *A, INT *Elt, INT i, INT verbose_level);
1192 };

2218  INT *gen_depth; // [nb_gen]
2219  INT *gen_perm; // [nb_gen]
2220 
2221  INT *nb_gen; // [base_len + 1]
2222  // nb_gen[i] is the number of generators
2223  // which stabilize the base points 0,...,i-1,
2224  // i.e. which belong to G^{(i)}.
2225  // The actual generator index ("gen_idx") must be obtained
2226  // from the array gen_perm[].
2227  // Thus, gen_perm[j] for 0 \le j < nb_gen[i] are the
2228  // indices of generators which belong to G^{(i)}
2229  // the generators for G^{(i)} modulo G^{(i+1)}
2230  // those indexed by nb_gen[i + 1], .., nb_gen[i] - 1 (!!!)
2231  // Observe that the entries in nb_gen[] are *decreasing*.
2232  // This is because the generators at the bottom of the
2233  // stabilizer chain are listed first.
2234  // (And nb_gen[0] is the total number of generators).
2235 
2236  INT *path; // [base_len]
2237 
2238  INT nb_images;
2239  INT **images;
2240 
2241  INT *orbit_len; // [base_len]
2242  // orbit_len[i] is the length of the i-th basic orbit.
2243 
2244  INT **orbit; // [base_len][A->deg]
2245  // orbit[i][j] is the j-th point in the orbit of the i-th base point.
2246  // for 0 \le j < orbit_len[i].
2247  // for orbit_len[i] \le j < A->deg, the points not in the orbit are listed.
2248  INT **orbit_inv; // [base_len][A->deg]
2249  // orbit[i] is the inverse of the permutation orbit[i],
2250  // i.e. given a point j,
2251  // orbit_inv[i][j] is the coset (or position in the orbit)
2252  // which contains j.
2253 
2254  INT **prev; // [base_len][A->deg]
2255  INT **label; // [base_len][A->deg]
